al energy distribution are rare in\nindividual QSOs. All new evidence here weighs strongly toward the binary\ninterpretation. Q2345+007 thus may represent the highest redshift example known\nof interaction-triggered but as-yet unmerged luminous AGN.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 4 Feb 2002 21:15:05 GMT"}],"update_date":"2009-11-07"}
